    <header class="article-header">
      <span class="tag">AI Coding</span>
      <h1>Claude Code vs Cursor 2026: Which AI Coding Assistant Is Better?</h1>
      <p class="meta">Updated July 2026</p>
    </header>

    <p class="lead">
      The AI coding assistant market has exploded in 2026, and two tools stand above the rest for developers who want serious AI-powered programming help: <strong>Claude Code</strong> from Anthropic and <strong>Cursor</strong> from Anysphere. Both tools have attracted millions of developers, but they take fundamentally different approaches to AI-assisted coding. Claude Code is a terminal-first AI agent that can autonomously navigate codebases, edit files, run commands, and debug issues. Cursor is an AI-native IDE built on VS Code that integrates intelligence directly into every part of the editing experience. After extensive hands-on testing across real-world projects, benchmark comparisons, and long-term daily usage, here is the detailed breakdown you need to choose the right tool.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-top">
      <a href="https://claude.ai/code" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank">Try Claude Code Free →</a>
      <a href="https://cursor.sh" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank">Try Cursor Free →</a>
    </div>

    <h2>Claude Code vs Cursor: Quick Comparison</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Claude Code</th><th>Cursor</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Best For</td><td>Large codebases, autonomous tasks, terminal workflows</td><td>Integrated IDE experience, rapid inline coding</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Pricing</td><td>$20/mo (Pro), $100/mo (Max)</td><td>$20/mo (Pro), $40/user/mo (Business)</td></tr>
